# Code Standards

See also: `date-time-pickers.mdc` (picker UX) and `ui-theme.mdc` (theme tokens & UI consistency).

- Functional components only. No class components.
- RTK Query for all API calls. No raw fetch/axios anywhere in screens
  or components — if a call doesn't fit RTK Query's pattern, build a
  custom base query, don't bypass the layer.
- React Hook Form + Zod for all forms, no exceptions, including
  single-field forms (search bars with validation, etc.)
- FlatList (or FlashList if already adopted) with stable, unique keys.
  Never use array index as key. List items must be memoized
  (`React.memo` or equivalent) when the list can exceed ~20 items.
- Every screen with async data: loading, error, AND empty states.
  A screen with only a happy path is incomplete, not "good enough for now."
- `expo-secure-store` for JWT and any credential-like value. Never
  AsyncStorage for tokens.
- Hard bans: `any` type, class components, inline style objects,
  index-as-key, hardcoded color/spacing values, raw fetch for API data.
- Soft rule: comments explain *why*, not *what* — if a comment just
  restates the code, remove it.
- Tests: write them where they catch a real regression risk (payment
  flows, RLS-sensitive queries, role-gating logic). Don't write tests
  for trivial render-only components just to hit a coverage number.

## Self-check before presenting any change as complete

- Does this introduce a new pattern instead of using an existing one?
  If yes, flag it explicitly and explain why, don't silently diverge.
- Did I touch a file outside the scope of what was asked? If yes,
  call it out separately rather than bundling it into the same diff
  silently.
